 something happens when I write and it gets all bad....Please crit this small part of a story I started. Sorry ahead for the confusion and missing parts of a plot.<br>
<br>
Ray was pulling on the trucks door handle as Shraik and Max locked the garage doors. <br>
&quot;Max, get over here.&quot; Ray called as the gunfire from outside grew louder. Shraik glanced around the rather resourceful garage. Shraik heard Ray and Max talking, gunfire, and glass breaking. He turned to see the trucks' driver window shattered. Max climbed up into the window and fumbled around inside. Shraik couldn't find his sword, so he looked for something else. <br>
&quot;Found them!&quot; Max called out from the truck as he held up a set of keys. Shraik walked up to the desk with the cluttered papers over it and opened the drawer.<br>
&quot;Ooh! Shiny gun!&quot; He said and hopped into the back of the truck. Ray went into the drivers side and Max into the passenger.<br>
<br>
Bullets were flying through the flimsy garage doors as Ray started the engine. Shraik dived down on his side after a loud clang noise and a light appeared inches from his face. &quot;Hurry, Ray!&quot; Max cried as more bullets hit the truck. Ray put the car in reverse and turned towards the garage doors. Shraik tightened his sweaty grip on the handgun. <br>
<br>
Max Burner hadn't been so excited in his short 11 year old life. He'd barely knew this Shraik guy for a month and they were already diving into action. <br>
&quot;Get down guys!&quot; Ray yelled and Max ducked as low as he could. Screeching tires and loud crashes were all Max heard.<br>
<br>
Shraik crouched low in the back in the pickup but peeked up every few seconds. Ray ran the truck through the doors making them collapse, luckily not on Shraik. Almost as soon as Ray made it through Shraik started firing. PG's we're all around the huge hall, and they were all firing at the truck.<br>
<br>
Ray Wallman looked through the rearview mirror and sighed.<br>
&quot;Why are they attacking us?!&quot; Max seemed to like the action. Ray looked forward and gasped, a wall was right in front of them and was coming closer.<br>
<br>
Something seems wrong..... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=samspade>samspade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(2/26/02 5:16:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=527.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Excerpt from my story...Critique please</span><hr size=1> Hate to do the psychologist trick but what do you think is wrong with it?<br>
