 <p>Life is just one damn thing after another - Frank Ward O’Malley</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=samspade>samspade</A> at: 2/26/02 5:18:01 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ugothicchaos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>gothic chaos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(2/26/02 5:36:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=527.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Excerpt from my story...Critique please</span><hr size=1> To me, it seems to lack personality. Specifically in the way the characters speak. For example, when one of them says &quot;Ooh, shiney ect...&quot; it might add a bit of intrest to describe how he said this. Was it in a mishchiviouse(sp?) manner, or an excited one. Did his eyes widen in joy, or did he smile because of his good fortune? <br>
<br>
I say this because when I was reading it, the mental picture I got was three people in grey speaking in monotone voices. Work on including this, it will help add to your characters personality and help the reader get a better picture.<br>
<br>
Concerning the plot so far, it doesn't seem to be going wrong. I personally want to know what an 11 year old is doing hanging out with people who get shot at?<br>
<br>
