pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=527.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> heck</span><hr size=1> I'm gonna put a later part in the scene that I just sort of revised.<br>
<br>
Shraik didn't need to scream to get Ray to stop the truck. The tires squealed as the trucks front bumper tapped anothers rear one. Max was gasping for breath.<br>
&quot;Wh...What?&quot; Ray held his chest and said hoarsely, &quot;Where'd they come from?&quot; Shraik shut his eyes tightly and opened them, that usually helped him in confusing situations, he never knew why. Max shivered and sunk down in the seat, &quot;What's happening?&quot; Shraik took deep breaths as he climbed from the back of the pickup, which was now stained with bulletholes. <br>
<br>
Cars, trucks, vehicles. They were everywhere on the road. Ray shook his head and put his hands over his face. The gun was in Shraiks shaky and sweaty grip. Max was trying to stay calm. A few moments before, the road was deserted, and suddenly the automobiles road in from behind shrubbery or trees and made a huge traffic jam. Shraik stated in a cautious voice what Max and Ray already knew, &quot;They don't want us to leave.&quot;<br>
<br>
Shraik Moode, with wide and curious eyes stepped toward the closest car. A small green Volkswagen, or 'punch buggy' as many people called them. A rough looking man was inside it, looked to be about 45. He had a salt and pepper colored beard and round sunglasses over his eyes. The man wore a cowboy hat that looked as worn as him. Shraik found it most strange that the man didn't even notice him standing outside his window. Shraik looked back at Ray and Max who were in the truck, they nervously nodded, then turned back to the window. He said in the most normal voice he could,&quot; Excuse me, sir! Can you tell me... What's happening?&quot;<br>
<br>
The man didn't reply, he didn't even move, but the window rolled down. &quot;Sir... Can you please...&quot; Shraik said in a half exasperate voice. The man turned his head to face Shraik and smiled. Shraik backed up and managed to force a smile. The man opened the door and stepped out. Shraik gasped at the size of the shotgun. It was bigger than most he had ever seen. But the man held it with ease, and aimed it. <br>
<br>
